<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4404</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lindsay</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-16">July 16, 1931</date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In replying to your
                                communication of July 10, 1931, concerning the meeting in London on
                                July 17 of financial experts, I have to inform you that Mr. Hugh
                                Gibson, American Ambassador at Brussels, Belgium, will be the
                                representative of this Government at the meeting in question. His
                                function, in view of the character of the discussions which will
                                take place, will be largely that of an observer.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Castle,
                                Jr.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>